snippet: In the Chamber Music Society’s “Great Clarinet Quintets” program, Marc Neikrug’s Clarinet Quintet for David Shifrin received its New York premiere.
abstract: Vivien Schweitzer reviews Chamber Music Society's program of great clarinet quintets, featuring New York premiere of piece composed by Marc Neikrug, performed by David Shifrin and the Orion String Quartet at Alice Tully Hall.
lead_paragraph: In the Chamber Music Society’s “Great Clarinet Quintets” program, Marc Neikrug’s Clarinet Quintet for David Shifrin received its New York premiere.
